{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.31",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 31,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 31 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:1",
      "text": "Wakefulness that comes from riches consumes the flesh, and anxiety about it takes away sleep.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:2",
      "text": "Wakeful anxiety will crave slumber. In a severe disease, sleep will be broken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:3",
      "text": "A rich man toils in gathering money together. When he rests, he is filled with his good things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:4",
      "text": "A poor man toils in lack of substance. When he rests, he becomes needy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:5",
      "text": "He who loves gold won’t be justified. He who follows destruction will himself have his fill of it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:6",
      "text": "Many have been given over to ruin for the sake of gold. Their destruction meets them face to face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:7",
      "text": "It is a stumbling block to those who sacrifice to it. Every fool will be taken by it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:8",
      "text": "Blessed is the rich person who is found blameless, and who doesn’t go after gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:9",
      "text": "Who is he, that we may call him blessed? For he has done wonderful things among his people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:10",
      "text": "Who has been tried by it, and found perfect? Then let him boast. Who has had the power to transgress, and has not transgressed? And to do evil, and has not done it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:11",
      "text": "His prosperity will be made sure. The congregation will proclaim his alms.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:12",
      "text": "Do you sit at a great table? Don’t be greedy there. Don’t say, “There is a lot of food on it!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:13",
      "text": "Remember that a greedy eye is a wicked thing. What has been created more greedy than an eye? Therefore it sheds tears from every face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:14",
      "text": "Don’t stretch your hand wherever it looks. Don’t thrust yourself with it into the dish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:15",
      "text": "Consider your neighbor’s feelings by your own. Be discreet in every point.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:16",
      "text": "Eat like a human being those things which are set before you. Don’t eat greedily, lest you be hated.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:17",
      "text": "Be first to stop for manners’ sake. Don’t be insatiable, lest you offend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:18",
      "text": "And if you sit among many, Don’t reach out your hand before them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:19",
      "text": "How sufficient to a well-mannered man is a very little. He doesn’t breathe heavily in his bed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:20",
      "text": "Healthy sleep comes from moderate eating. He rises early, and his wits are with him. The pain of wakefulness, colic, and griping are with an insatiable man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:21",
      "text": "And if you have been forced to eat, rise up in the middle of it, and you shall have rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:22",
      "text": "Hear me, my son, and don’t despise me, and in the end you will appreciate my words. In all your works be skillful, and no disease will come to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:23",
      "text": "People bless him who is liberal with his food. The testimony of his excellence will be believed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:24",
      "text": "The city will murmur at him who is a stingy with his food. The testimony of his stinginess will be accurate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:25",
      "text": "Don’t show yourself valiant in wine, for wine has destroyed many.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:26",
      "text": "The furnace tests the temper of steel by dipping; so does wine test hearts in the quarreling of the proud.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:27",
      "text": "Wine is as good as life to men, if you drink it in moderation. What life is there to a man who is without wine? It has been created to make men glad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:28",
      "text": "Wine drunk in season and in moderation is joy of heart and gladness of soul:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:29",
      "text": "Wine drunk excessively is bitterness of soul, with provocation and conflict.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:30",
      "text": "Drunkenness increases the rage of a fool to his hurt. It diminishes strength and adds wounds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.31.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 31:31",
      "text": "Don’t rebuke your neighbor at a banquet of wine. Don’t despise him in his mirth. Don’t speak a word of reproach to him. Don’t distress him by making demands of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
